eep him alive, but now he will have some minions you need to deal with.  You can't usually mez or root these things reliably, which means you need to have, guess what?  Some more clerics to keep people alive while they deal with the extras.<br><br>This is probably my biggest gripe about EQ, the reliance on so many clerics to kill stuff.  Want to try the Avatar of War?  Experts say you better plan on having a bare minimum of EIGHT clerics for this job, allthough most guilds use lots more.   What mob in the entire game needs you to have EIGHT of any other classes?  Can you imagine having to round up 8 rangers or 8 shadowknights just to get into the ring with something?<br><br>Here's the concensus &quot;best&quot; EQ guild running, Fires of Heaven on the Veeshan server's roster.  <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://fohguild.org/flash/fohmembers2.swf">fohguild.org/flash/fohmembers2.swf</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>17 clerics, 14 warriors, 11 monks, 10 wizards, 8 rogues, 4 rangers, 2 necros, 3 mages ... you get the idea.  This isn't an accident, the best guild feels they need 8 times as many clerics as necromancers.  ironically, the role of the necromancer and mage on certan big bosses is delegated to giving the clerics even more mana!<br><br>So this is my rant.  What's up with needing so many clerics?  no other class even comes remotely close.  <br><br>This sounds pretty wild but why not just give druids and shamans Complete Heal?  That way it wouldn't be quite so hard to round up so many CHers.  Heaven forbid the cleric is only there for aegolism while the druids and shaman do all the healing.  A role that many other &quot;support classes&quot; have had to live with a long time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align=