eqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2449.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reliance on clerics</span><hr size=1> This issue has been the focus of a petition put in by the Druid community for Verant.  Druid and Shaman-types are supposed to be backup healers, but with each new upgrade, we have lost our ability to do that more and more.<br><br>I like being a druid very much - I enjoy the flexibility.  We are not built to be the best at anything, but we are built to be the 2nd or 3rd best at almost everything - it's the nature of the class.  We can fill in where needed.  However, there is no way I can be an effective backup healer anymore.  Class balancing has passed us by.<br><br>I have no desire for my Druid to be a cleric - I just want to be able to effectively fill in when needed.  <br><br>Giving Druids a complete heal was suggested in this petition, or pumping up the effectiveness of Chloroblast was another suggestion. It will be interesting to see what happens in PoP and if Verant is paying attention.   <p><br><br><center><img src=http://www.36pix.com/00/129/41/preview/ed86c6aae9pSIYTYPoEYj0FAhBcDuLauSqY.jpg></center><center>51st Season Wanderer<br>Servant of Tunare<br><br>Calibriede Danu<br>21st Season Rogue of Tunare</center><br><br>Fear (1)  Hate (1)  Naggy (1)   Vox (1)   Currently renting a condo in Kael<br><br><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/uerrtai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Errtai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here...get out</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/22/02 4:07:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2449.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reliance on clerics</span><hr size=1> Think about all the different stuff you can raid in EQ.  <br><br>Is there any time you say, &quot;we cant do this without a shadowknight?  Or a paladin?&quot;<br><br>How often do you say, we don't have enough clerics?  Or we don't have a high enough level warrior to tank it.<br><br>Pallies and SKs are another topic.  One suggesiton for SKs is to give them a good class buff, like the ranger have Call of Predator and pallies have Divine Strength.  Where's the SK buff?  Even beastlords get spiritual purity/savagery, all the hybrids are covered except SKs.<br><br>I'm not saying any class is bad or useless, I'm just saying you never have to cancel a raid because no paladins and SKs are there.  You probably have to cancel if you get no clerics.  Hell, if you might have to cancel against AOW if you &quot;only&quot; get 6 or 7 clerics. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/udiirkshade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Diirk Shade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/22/02 4:12:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2449.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reliance on clerics</span><hr size=1> shrug, the problem is that eq was a game designed around a lvl 50 limit, and then sloppily hacked and patched up to 60 levels that become increasingly imbalanced...<br><br>What other class in the games uses a lvl 39 spells as their main spell at level 60? (no, rangers and sow doesn't count ;P)<br><br>Complete heal as it stands is the single biggest reason why the eq end game is screwed up beyond belief.. unfortunately, its far too late to change things now. <p></p>